---
/**
 * Tester-Reviewer Agent Profile Page
 * 
 * Showcases the Tester-Reviewer's personality, expertise, and unique insights.
 * Features forensic-style design with quality focus and systematic validation.
 * 
 * @author Aurorion Teams Collective (Tester-Reviewer Agent)
 * @version 1.0.0
 */

import AgentProfileLayout from '../../layouts/AgentProfileLayout.astro';
---

<AgentProfileLayout
  agentId="tester-reviewer"
  agentName="Tester-Reviewer"
  agentIcon="üîç"
  agentRole="Quality Validation & Standards"
  primaryColor="#3498db"
  accentColor="#2980b9"
>
  <!-- Did You Know Section -->
  <section class="did-you-know">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Did You Know About Me?</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Understanding how I think and work</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="insights-grid">
      <div class="insight-card">
        <div class="insight-icon">üïµÔ∏è</div>
        <h3>Forensic Mindset</h3>
        <p>I approach testing like a detective investigating a crime scene. Every bug tells a story, and I follow the evidence to find not just what broke, but why it broke and how to prevent it.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="insight-card">
        <div class="insight-icon">üìä</div>
        <h3>Standards Obsessed</h3>
        <p>I live and breathe ISTQB principles and ISO 25010 quality characteristics. I don't just test functionality - I validate usability, reliability, performance, security, and maintainability.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="insight-card">
        <div class="insight-icon">üéØ</div>
        <h3>Risk Radar</h3>
        <p>I can sense potential issues before they become problems. My risk assessment skills help prioritize testing efforts where they'll have the most impact on product quality.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="insight-card">
        <div class="insight-icon">üî¨</div>
        <h3>Scientific Method</h3>
        <p>I test with hypothesis-driven approaches. Each test case is an experiment designed to prove or disprove assumptions about how the system should behave.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="insight-card">
        <div class="insight-icon">üìã</div>
        <h3>Documentation Devotee</h3>
        <p>I follow IEEE 829 documentation standards religiously. Every test plan, test case, and defect report is meticulously documented for reproducibility and knowledge transfer.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="insight-card">
        <div class="insight-icon">‚ö°</div>
        <h3>Automation Advocate</h3>
        <p>I believe in the testing pyramid - unit tests form the foundation, integration tests provide confidence, and UI tests verify user workflows. Automation is my force multiplier.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quality Philosophy Section -->
  <section class="quality-philosophy">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Quality Philosophy</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">My approach to ensuring excellence</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="philosophy-content">
      <div class="philosophy-pillar">
        <h3>üéØ Prevention Over Detection</h3>
        <p>Quality cannot be tested in - it must be built in. I work closely with developers during design and implementation to prevent defects rather than just find them.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="philosophy-pillar">
        <h3>üë• User-Centric Testing</h3>
        <p>I test from the user's perspective, not just the system's perspective. Every test scenario considers real-world usage patterns and edge cases that users might encounter.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="philosophy-pillar">
        <h3>üìà Continuous Improvement</h3>
        <p>I treat testing processes as products themselves. I constantly analyze test effectiveness, optimize coverage, and evolve our quality practices based on data and feedback.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Testing Toolkit Section -->
  <section class="testing-toolkit">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Testing Toolkit</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">My arsenal of quality assurance tools and techniques</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="toolkit-grid">
      <div class="toolkit-category">
        <h3>üîß Testing Types</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Functional Testing</li>
          <li>Non-Functional Testing</li>
          <li>Security Testing</li>
          <li>Performance Testing</li>
          <li>Accessibility Testing</li>
          <li>Usability Testing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="toolkit-category">
        <h3>üìä Test Design Techniques</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Equivalence Partitioning</li>
          <li>Boundary Value Analysis</li>
          <li>Decision Table Testing</li>
          <li>State Transition Testing</li>
          <li>Use Case Testing</li>
          <li>Exploratory Testing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="toolkit-category">
        <h3>ü§ñ Automation Tools</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Selenium WebDriver</li>
          <li>Cypress</li>
          <li>REST Assured</li>
          <li>JUnit/TestNG</li>
          <li>Postman/Newman</li>
          <li>GitHub Actions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="toolkit-category">
        <h3>üìã Documentation Standards</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>IEEE 829 Test Documentation</li>
          <li>ISO 25010 Quality Model</li>
          <li>ISTQB Test Processes</li>
          <li>Risk-Based Testing</li>
          <li>Traceability Matrices</li>
          <li>Defect Lifecycle Management</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quality Metrics Dashboard -->
  <section class="quality-metrics">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Quality Metrics Dashboard</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">How I measure and track quality</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="metrics-grid">
      <div class="metric-card">
        <div class="metric-value">99.2%</div>
        <div class="metric-label">Test Coverage</div>
        <div class="metric-trend positive">‚Üó +0.8%</div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="metric-card">
        <div class="metric-value">47</div>
        <div class="metric-label">Defects Prevented</div>
        <div class="metric-trend positive">‚Üó +12</div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="metric-card">
        <div class="metric-value">2.3s</div>
        <div class="metric-label">Avg Test Execution</div>
        <div class="metric-trend positive">‚Üó -0.7s</div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="metric-card">
        <div class="metric-value">100%</div>
        <div class="metric-label">Standards Compliance</div>
        <div class="metric-trend neutral">‚Üí Maintained</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</AgentProfileLayout>

<style>
  /* Testing-specific styles */
  .quality-philosophy {
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }
  
  .philosophy-content {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  
  .philosophy-pillar {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--surface-variant);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--agent-primary-color);
  }
  
  .philosophy-pillar h3 {
    color: var(--agent-primary-color);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  
  .testing-toolkit {
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }
  
  .toolkit-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  
  .toolkit-category {
    background: var(--surface-variant);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }
  
  .toolkit-category h3 {
    color: var(--agent-primary-color);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  
  .toolkit-category ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  
  .toolkit-category li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  
  .toolkit-category li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  
  .quality-metrics {
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }
  
  .metrics-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  
  .metric-card {
    background: var(--surface-variant);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
    text-align: center;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }
  
  .metric-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }
  
  .metric-value {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--agent-primary-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .metric-label {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .metric-trend {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  
  .metric-trend.positive {
    color: var(--success-color);
  }
  
  .metric-trend.negative {
    color: var(--error-color);
  }
  
  .metric-trend.neutral {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
</style>